    <has_dmc>Yes</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study is part of a research program too see if amikacin delivered as an aerosol directly
      to the lungs in combination with IV antibiotic therapy can help intubated patients with
      gram-negative pneumonia get better faster than when given intravenous antibiotics alone. The
      primary purpose of this study is to determine the correct dose of amikacin which is delivered
      directly to the lungs as an aerosol via an investigational device called the Pulmonary
      Delivery Device System (PDDS).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
